This function does not exist in the official documentation that you have send, so probably it still doesn&#39;t exist. If you need something like that you should probably calculate the standard deviation by yourself programmaticaly. You have the [AVG function][1] that helps you get at least the median value which will be helpful in the calculation of the standard deviation and the [COUNT][2] function for the number of entries.
    
    double standardDeviation ; // standard deviation
    double sumOfDiffrences = 0; 
    
    for ( int i = 0; i &lt; count; i++ ){

    sumOfDiffrences = sumOfDiffrences + pow((entry(i)-avg),2); // entry(i) is an entry of the column you want to create the S.D.

    }
    standardDeviation = sqrt((sumOfDiffrences)/(count-1));

  [1]: https://cloud.google.com/spanner/docs/functions-and-operators#avg
  [2]: https://cloud.google.com/spanner/docs/functions-and-operators#count

